  "title": "Florida Firefighters Rescued a 'Dog.' It Was a Coyote.",
  "script": "Not a dog — a coyote! Cape Coral, Florida got a 911 call: a dog was drowning in Britannia Lake. A neighbor named Brian jumped in to help. Another neighbor, Denae Judd, grabbed her kayak and paddled out. Firefighters waded in. Everyone assumed they were saving a dog. Then they pulled it out. It was a coyote pup. Soaking wet, exhausted, and furious. Too worn out to release, they rushed it to the vet. Turns out the pup had fallen in. Brian saw it happen, jumped in — and his splash drew the crowd that called 911. Denae and Brian both got a Community Recognition Coin from the Cape Coral Fire Department. So who saved whom here — did a coyote just trick an entire Florida neighborhood into an emergency response?",
